# TypeScript Bot Conventions

- Match existing style: classes, private methods, chalk `Logger`, `async/await`
- Minimal scope — fix only what the task requires
- No new dependencies without explicit user approval
- Use existing `config` types from `src/config.ts`; extend interfaces there when needed
- Error messages: include context (`@${username}`, action name); log via `logger.error`
- Do not add tests unless requested

```typescript
// BAD — silent catch
try { await page.click(selector); } catch (e) {}

// GOOD — log and rethrow or return status
try { await page.click(selector); } catch (e: any) {
  this.logger.error(`Click failed on comment button: ${e.message}`);
  return 'FAILED';
}
```
